track_notes: Park at the Rough Butt Bald Overlook on the Blue Ridge Parkway.  Take the short connector trail across the road from the parking lot.  Take a right on the Mountains to Sea Trail.
track_title: W4C/WM-006 - Mt Hardy - Eastbound on the MST

track_notes: Park at gravel lot where the Mountains to Sea trail crosses Hwy 215.
track_title: W4C/WM-006 - Mt Hardy - Westbound on MST

track_notes: 0.9 mile hike with 600 EG.  This unmarked and unmaintained trail is the shortest route to Mt Hardy.  Many people have had difficulty navigating this trail in either direction.  Heading south on the BRP, park where convenient after the paved drainage ditch in Mt Hardy Gap (35.299231, -82.924847).  The trail enters the woods above the paved drainage ditch on the embankment.  The trail is easy to follow for most of the way, but be prepared for blowdowns along the trail.  When the trail enters an open area under a rock face, it meanders a bit up and down the slope but generally maintains the contour.  It does this for 100 yards or so and then heads up hill to the Mt Hardy trail (bascially at the end of the open rock face).  When coming back down the Mt Hardy trail, the start of this trail can be difficult to spot but is in the middle of a rather sharp S-turn on the trail.
track_title: Mt Hardy via Mt Hardy Gap

track_notes: This approach is less steep than the shortest route, but somewhat longer. It is quite a bit shorter than the approaches using the Mountains to Sea Trail from the parkway. A good parking spot can be found at N 35.2994, W 082.9225.
